        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(copilot): guard against undefined runtime.state during cli-metadata registration",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #94516: `@openclaw/copilot` crashes at startup with `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'openSyncKeyedStore')`.\n\nTwo-layer fix:\n\n**Layer B (api-builder.ts)** — Universal safety net. All plugins are protected from a bare `{}` runtime regardless of registration path.\n\n**Layer C (copilot/index.ts)** — Mode-aware guard. Copilot is a full-runtime plugin (registers an agent harness), so metadata-only paths (`cli-metadata`, `discovery`, `setup-only`) skip registration. The full gateway activation path will pick it up later. Uses `api.registrationMode !== \"full\"` (the public SDK contract) instead of checking runtime internals.\n\n**Layer — (loader.ts)** The existing `createMetadataRuntime()` stub provides a real in-memory store for metadata paths that do need `openSyncKeyedStore`.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nClawSweeper review (#95229) requested:\n- [P1] Gate Copilot registration by `api.registrationMode` instead of `runtime.state` shape\n- [P1] \"updating api\" — ensure `runtime.state` is never undefined\n\nThis PR implements both, plus retains the loader-level stub.\n\n## Evidence\n\n`node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/copilot/index.test.ts`\n\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  5 passed (5)\n```\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- [x] No new dependencies\n- [x] No config surface changes\n- [x] No API contract changes\n- [x] Copilot tests pass\n- [x] Full-runtime failures stay loud (throws clear errors, not silent undefined)\n- [x] Additive — existing runtime paths untouched\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review / ClawSweeper re-review\n\nWhat is still waiting?\n- CI (Crabbox) on maintainer approval\n\nWhich bot comments were addressed?\n- [P2] Gate by `api.registrationMode !== \"full\"` → done\n- [P1] Safe `runtime.state` in `buildPluginApi` → done\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Fix copilot registration crash when `runtime.state` is absent on metadata-only registration paths\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node 24.13.1, Linux x86_64\n\n**Command run**:\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/copilot/index.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  5 passed (5)\n```\n\n**Observed result**: 5/5 tests pass. The `registrationMode` guard correctly skips non-full paths, and the `safeRuntime` proxy in `buildPluginApi` prevents any future plugin from hitting `undefined` state.\n\n**What was not tested**: Full `openclaw plugins list` with npm-installed copilot (no registry access)\n",
